node.text: Bungee jump over Northern Europe’s deepest canyon- 153 meters!🥶🏞 Who’d like to experience this?📍Gorsabrua, Norway🇳🇴 Video by @andreabadendyck

A bike ride in Paradise!🌟🚴 Who’d you like to cycle with here?😍 by @matiasderada 📍Salar de Uyuni, Bolivia🇧🇴 

📌 Salar de Uyuni in southwest Bolivia, is the world’s largest salt flat. It’s the legacy of a prehistoric lake that went dry, leaving behind a desertlike, nearly 11,000-square km. landscape of bright-white salt, rock formations and cacti-studded islands. Its otherworldly expanse can be observed from central Incahuasi Island. Though wildlife is rare in this unique ecosystem, it harbors many pink flamingos. This epic salt flat has a desert like feel and it might look like a frozen lake, but it’s covered in bright salt all over.🌅
